White House officials, including Domestic Policy Advisor Susan Rice, Director of Public Engagement and Senior Advisor Cedric Richmond, Chief of Staff to the Vice President Tina Flournoy, and National Security Council Senior Director for the Western Hemisphere Juan Gonzalez, met with members of the Congressional Black Caucus to discuss the ongoing efforts to address irregular migration in Del Rio, TX and ensure Haitian migrants are treated with dignity and respect. The Congressional Black Caucus members emphasized the importance of supporting the Haitian people and Haitian diaspora in an equitable manner. The White House officials highlighted President Biden's commitment to implementing a safe, humane, and orderly immigration process, as well as providing aid to the Haitian people. The United States has recently provided $32 million in new assistance to support earthquake response efforts in Haiti, in addition to $75.5 million in bilateral development and health assistance announced in January 2021. The United States has made over $5.1 billion available for assistance to Haiti since the 2010 earthquake. The participants pledged to continue an open dialogue on the situation. This meeting is part of a series of discussions between White House officials and community leaders.